<recipe>
  <name>Pedernales River Chili</name>
  <safe_name>Pedernales_River_Chili</safe_name>
  <yield_count></yield_count>
  <yield_measure></yield_measure>
  <notes>The paper claims a lineage from Lady Bird Johnson and is allegedly verifiable on the LBJ online library (lbjlib.utexas.edu > research > reference > quick facts > recipes).

Chili meat is defined for us here as "coursley gorund round steak or a well-rimmed chuck".

According to the article, Lady Bird came up with this after LBJ had his first heart attack.  Surprisingly he continued to live through this much sodium.  Ole!</notes>
  <prep_time></prep_time>
  <ingredients>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>4 lb</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>chili meat</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>large onion</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>chopped</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 cloves</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>garlic</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>ground oregano</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>ground cumin (comino)</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>6 tsp</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>chili powder</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>additional to taste</preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>1 1/2 cups</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>channed whole tomatoes</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2-6 dashes</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>hot sauce</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>2 cups</quantity>
      <ingredient_name>hot water</ingredient_name>
      <preparation></preparation>
    </ingredient>
    <ingredient>
      <quantity></quantity>
      <ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
      <preparation>to taste</preparation>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
  <preparation>Brown meat and cook onion and garlic until translucent in a large heavy pan or Dutch Oven.  Add oregano, ground cumin, tomatoes, hot pepper sauce, salt and hot water  and bring mixture to a boil before simmering one hour.  Skim off fat during cooking.</preparation>
